{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849554793,"sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","part":{"id":"prt_d78e1b7740012vi5c8BFHk2U2e","messageID":"msg_d78e19e46001FcnbJ2ANajOOOM","sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6436dfaf86434ca0a73b1688d05e0285","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The Router HTTP reverse proxy core provides session-aware routing for AgentCube sandbox invocations. It resolves sessions via the store, creates new sandboxes through the Workload Manager when needed, reverse-proxies HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints, injects JWT tokens for sandbox authentication, and tracks activity for idle timeout detection.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\n23: Ōöé                              AgentCube Cluster                               Ōöé\n24: Ōöé  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ                                                             Ōöé\n25: Ōöé  Ōöé Client/SDK  Ōöé                                                             Ōöé\n26: Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś                                                             Ōöé\n27: Ōöé         Ōöé HTTP + x-agentcube-session-id                                      Ōöé\n28: Ōöé         Ō¢╝                                                                     Ōöé\n29: Ōöé  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ Ōöé\n30: Ōöé  Ōöé                        Router (pkg/router)                              Ōöé Ōöé\n31: Ōöé  Ōöé  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ  Ōöé Ōöé\n32: Ōöé  Ōöé  Ōöé   Server    Ōöé  ŌöéSessionManager Ōöé  ŌöéJWTManager  Ōöé  Ōöé ReverseProxy  Ōöé  Ōöé Ōöé\n33: Ōöé  Ōöé  Ōöé  (Gin)      Ōöé  Ōöé               Ōöé  Ōöé            Ōöé  Ōöé               Ōöé  Ōöé Ōöé\n34: Ōöé  Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś  Ōöé Ōöé\n35: Ōöé  Ōöé         Ōöé                 Ōöé                 Ōöé                 Ōöé          Ōöé Ōöé\n36: Ōöé  Ōöé  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ¢╝ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ  Ōöé Ōöé\n37: Ōöé  Ōöé  Ōöé                     Middleware Stack                               Ōöé  Ōöé Ōöé\n38: Ōöé  Ōöé  Ōöé  Logger ŌåÆ Recovery ŌåÆ ConcurrencyLimit                              Ōöé  Ōöé Ōöé\n39: Ōöé  Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś  Ōöé Ōöé\n40: Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś Ōöé\n41: Ōöé             Ōöé                                    Ōöé                            Ōöé\n42: Ōöé             Ō¢╝                                    Ō¢╝                            Ōöé\n43: Ōöé  ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ               ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ            Ōöé\n44: Ōöé  Ōöé  Redis/Valkey    Ōöé               Ōöé    Workload Manager        Ōöé            Ōöé\n45: Ōöé  Ōöé  (Session Store) Ōöé               Ōöé    (Sandbox Creation)      Ōöé            Ōöé\n46: Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś               ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś            Ōöé\n47: Ōöé                                                     Ōöé                         Ōöé\n48: Ōöé                                                     Ō¢╝                         Ōöé\n49: Ōöé                                      ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ           Ōöé\n50: Ōöé                                      Ōöé  Kubernetes API Server     Ōöé           Ōöé\n51: Ōöé                                      Ōöé  (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)     Ōöé           Ōöé\n52: Ōöé                                      ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌö¼ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś           Ōöé\n53: Ōöé                                                    Ōöé                          Ōöé\n54: Ōöé                                                    Ō¢╝                          Ōöé\n55: Ōöé                                      ŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ           Ōöé\n56: Ōöé                                      Ōöé      Sandbox Pods          Ōöé           Ōöé\n57: Ōöé                                      Ōöé  (Target Endpoints)        Ōöé           Ōöé\n58: Ōöé                                      ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś           Ōöé\n59: Ōöé  ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś Ōöé\n60: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöś\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Request Flow\n64: \n65: ```\n66: 1. Client Request ŌåÆ Router Server\n67:    Ōöé\n68: 2. Middleware Chain (Logger ŌåÆ Recovery ŌåÆ ConcurrencyLimit)\n69:    Ōöé\n70: 3. Route Handler (handleInvoke)\n71:    Ōöé\n72: 4. Session Resolution (SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession)\n73:    Ōö£ŌöĆ Header present ŌåÆ Store lookup\n74:    ŌööŌöĆ Header empty ŌåÆ Workload Manager POST ŌåÆ Store save\n75:    Ōöé\n76: 5. Last-Activity Update (store.UpdateSessionLastActivity)\n77:    Ōöé\n78: 6. Entry Point Selection (SandboxInfo.EntryPoints matching)\n79:    Ōöé\n80: 7. JWT Generation (JWTManager.GenerateToken) [for Sandbox/SandboxClaim]\n81:    Ōöé\n82: 8. Reverse Proxy (httputil.ReverseProxy)\n83:    Ōö£ŌöĆ Director: path normalization, forwarding headers, JWT\n84:    ŌööŌöĆ ErrorHandler: 502/504 error mapping\n85:    Ōöé\n86: 9. Response Header Injection (x-agentcube-session-id)\n87:    Ōöé\n88: 10. Last-Activity Update (after proxy completion)\n89:    Ōöé\n90: 11. Response ŌåÆ Client\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Design\n96: \n97: ### Component Relationships\n98: \n99: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n100: |-----------|------|--------------|\n101: | `Server` | Gin HTTP server, route registration, lifecycle management | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `JWTManager`, `http.Transport` |\n102: | `SessionManager` | Session resolution, sandbox creation via Workload Manager | `Store`, Workload Manager HTTP client |\n103: | `JWTManager` | RS256 JWT generation, K8s Secret persistence | `kubernetes.Interface`, RSA keys |\n104: | `ReverseProxy` | HTTP forwarding to sandbox pods, header injection | `http.Transport`, `JWTManager` |\n105: | `Middleware` | Concurrency limiting via semaphore | Config (`MaxConcurrentRequests`) |\n106: | `Handlers` | Health endpoints, invocation routing | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `ReverseProxy` |\n107: \n108: ### Dependencies\n109: \n110: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n111: |---------|---------|-------------|\n112: | Gin | HTTP framework, routing, middleware | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` |\n113: | JWT | RS256 JWT signing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n114: | HTTP2 | h2c server configuration | `golang.org/x/net/http2` |\n115: | Client-go | Kubernetes API client | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n116: | Klog | Structured logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n117: | Store | Session storage interface | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` |\n118: | Types | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n119: | APIErrors | Kubernetes API status errors | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Data Structures\n124: \n125: ### Config (`config.go`)\n126: \n127: ```go\n128: package router\n129: \n130: type Config struct {\n131:     Port                  string        // Listening port (e.g., \":8080\")\n132:     EnableTLS             bool          // Enable TLS\n133:     TLSCert               string        // TLS certificate file path\n134:     TLSKey                string        // TLS private key file path\n135:     MaxConcurrentRequests int           // Semaphore capacity (default 1000 when <=0)\n136:     Debug                 bool          // Gin debug mode\n137: }\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Defaults:**\n141: - `Port`: `\":8080\"`\n142: - `MaxConcurrentRequests`: `1000` (when value <= 0 in `NewServer`)\n143: \n144: ### Server (`server.go`)\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: type Server struct {\n148:     config         *Config\n149:     engine         *gin.Engine\n150:     httpServer     *http.Server\n151:     sessionManager SessionManager\n152:     storeClient    store.Store\n153:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n154:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n155: }\n156: ```\n157: \n158: **HTTP Server Configuration:**\n159: - `ReadTimeout`: 30s\n160: - `IdleTimeout`: 90s\n161: - H2C enabled via `http2.Server`\n162: \n163: ### SessionManager (`session_manager.go`)\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: type SessionManager interface {\n167:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n168: }\n169: \n170: type manager struct {\n171:     storeClient     store.Store\n172:     workloadMgrAddr string\n173:     httpClient      *http.Client\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: **HTTP Client Configuration:**\n178: - `Timeout`: 2m\n179: - `MaxIdleConnsPerHost`: 100\n180: - `DisableCompression`: false\n181: - HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n182: \n183: ### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n184: \n185: ```go\n186: type JWTManager struct {\n187:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n188:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n189:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: **Constants:**\n194: ```go\n195: const (\n196:     rsaKeySize          = 2048\n197:     jwtExpiration       = 5 * time.Minute\n198:     IdentitySecretName  = \"picod-router-identity\"\n199:     PrivateKeyDataKey   = \"private.pem\"\n200:     PublicKeyDataKey    = \"public.pem\"\n201: )\n202: \n203: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ### Error Types (`errors.go`)\n207: \n208: ```go\n209: type SessionNotFoundError struct {\n210:     SessionID string\n211: }\n212: \n213: type SandboxUnreachableError struct {\n214:     SandboxID string\n215: }\n216: \n217: type SandboxTimeoutError struct {\n218:     SandboxID string\n219: }\n220: \n221: type JWTSigningError struct {\n222:     Err error\n223: }\n224: \n225: type WorkloadManagerError struct {\n226:     StatusCode int\n227:     Message    string\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## API Contracts\n234: \n235: ### Route Table\n236: \n237: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n238: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n239: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n240: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n241: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n242: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n243: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n244: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n245: \n246: ### Session Manager Interface\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: type SessionManager interface {\n250:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: **Behavior:**\n255: - When `sessionID` is empty: POST to Workload Manager, store result, return `SandboxInfo`\n256: - When `sessionID` is non-empty: Lookup from store, return `SandboxInfo` or error\n257: \n258: **Workload Manager Endpoints:**\n259: - `AgentRuntime`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n260: - `CodeInterpreter`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter`\n261: \n262: ### JWT Manager Interface\n263: \n264: ```go\n265: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n266: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n267: func (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error\n268: ```\n269: \n270: **JWT Claims Structure:**\n271: ```go\n272: {\n273:     \"exp\": <now + 5m Unix>,\n274:     \"iat\": <now Unix>,\n275:     \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n276:     // + custom claims (e.g., \"session_id\")\n277: }\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ### Health Endpoints\n281: \n282: **Live Check (`GET /health/live`):**\n283: ```json\n284: {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n285: ```\n286: Status: 200\n287: \n288: **Ready Check (`GET /health/ready`):**\n289: ```json\n290: {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n291: ```\n292: Status: 200 (when sessionManager != nil)\n293: \n294: ```json\n295: {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n296: ```\n297: Status: 503 (when sessionManager == nil)\n298: \n299: ### Invocation Response Headers\n300: \n301: | Header | Value |\n302: |--------|-------|\n303: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Resolved session ID |\n304: \n305: ### Error Response Format\n306: \n307: ```json\n308: {\n309:     \"error\": \"<message>\",\n310:     \"code\": \"<error_code>\"\n311: }\n312: ```\n313: \n314: **Error Codes:**\n315: | Code | HTTP Status | Condition |\n316: |------|-------------|-----------|\n317: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Store lookup failed |\n318: | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Connection refused |\n319: | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Timeout during proxy |\n320: | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT generation failed |\n321: | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrency limit exhausted |\n322: | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | Empty EntryPoints in SandboxInfo |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Error Handling\n327: \n328: ### Proxy Error Mapping (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func proxyErrorHandler(resp http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, err error) {\n332:     errMsg := err.Error()\n333:     var statusCode int\n334:     var message string\n335:     \n336:     if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"connection refused\") {\n337:         statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n338:         message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n339:     } else if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"timeout\") {\n340:         statusCode = http.StatusGatewayTimeout\n341:         message = \"sandbox timeout\"\n342:     } else {\n343:         statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n344:         message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n345:     }\n346:     \n347:     resp.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n348:     resp.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n349:     json.NewEncoder(resp).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": message})\n350: }\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Handler Error Helper (`handlers.go`)\n354: \n355: ```go\n356: func handleGetSandboxError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n357:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n358:         c.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\"error\": err.Error()})\n359:         return\n360:     }\n361:     \n362:     if apiStatus, ok := err.(apierrors.APIStatus); ok {\n363:         code := int(apiStatus.Status().Code)\n364:         if code == 0 {\n365:             code = http.StatusInternalServerError\n366:         }\n367:         msg := apiStatus.Status().Message\n368:         if msg == \"\" {\n369:             msg = err.Error()\n370:         }\n371:         if code == http.StatusInternalServerError {\n372:             msg = \"internal server error\"\n373:         }\n374:         c.JSON(code, gin.H{\"error\": msg})\n375:         return\n376:     }\n377:     \n378:     c.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"internal server error\"})\n379: }\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ### Workload Manager Response Handling\n383: \n384: | HTTP Status | Error Type |\n385: |-------------|------------|\n386: | 404 | `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` |\n387: | Non-200 | `WorkloadManagerError` |\n388: | Empty `sessionId` in body | Internal error (validation) |\n389: \n390: ### Store Error Mapping\n391: \n392: | Store Error | HTTP Response |\n393: |-------------|---------------|\n394: | `store.ErrNotFound` | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n395: | Other errors | 500 internal server error |\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ## Reverse Proxy Implementation\n400: \n401: ### Director Function (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n402: \n403: ```go\n404: func director(req *http.Request, target *url.URL, jwt string) {\n405:     // Path normalization\n406:     path := req.URL.Path\n407:     if path != \"\" && path[0] != '/' {\n408:         path = \"/\" + path\n409:     }\n410:     \n411:     req.URL.Scheme = target.Scheme\n412:     req.URL.Host = target.Host\n413:     req.URL.Path = path\n414:     req.URL.RawPath = \"\"\n415:     req.Host = target.Host\n416:     \n417:     // Forwarding headers\n418:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Host\", req.Header.Get(\"Host\"))\n419:     proto := \"http\"\n420:     if req.TLS != nil {\n421:         proto = \"https\"\n422:     }\n423:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Proto\", proto)\n424:     \n425:     existingXFF := req.Header.Get(\"X-Forwarded-For\")\n426:     clientIP := req.RemoteAddr\n427:     if existingXFF != \"\" {\n428:         clientIP = existingXFF + \",\" + clientIP\n429:     }\n430:     req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-For\", clientIP)\n431:     \n432:     // JWT injection\n433:     if jwt != \"\" {\n434:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)\n435:     }\n436: }\n437: ```\n438: \n439: ### Entry Point Selection\n440: \n441: ```go\n442: func selectEntryPoint(entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint, invocationPath string) *types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n443:     if len(entryPoints) == 0 {\n444:         return nil\n445:     }\n446:     \n447:     // Find matching entry point by path prefix\n448:     for _, ep := range entryPoints {\n449:         if strings.HasPrefix(invocationPath, ep.Path) {\n450:             return &ep\n451:         }\n452:     }\n453:     \n454:     // Default to first entry point\n455:     return &entryPoints[0]\n456: }\n457: \n458: func buildTargetURL(ep *types.SandboxEntryPoint) *url.URL {\n459:     endpoint := ep.Endpoint\n460:     if ep.Protocol != \"\" && !strings.Contains(endpoint, \"://\") {\n461:         endpoint = strings.ToLower(ep.Protocol) + \"://\" + endpoint\n462:     }\n463:     return url.Parse(endpoint)\n464: }\n465: ```\n466: \n467: ---\n468: \n469: ## Middleware Implementation\n470: \n471: ### Concurrency Limit (`middleware.go`)\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int) gin.HandlerFunc {\n475:     if maxConcurrent <= 0 {\n476:         maxConcurrent = 1000\n477:     }\n478:     \n479:     sem := make(chan struct{}, maxConcurrent)\n480:     \n481:     return func(c *gin.Context) {\n482:         select {\n483:         case sem <- struct{}{}:\n484:             defer func() { <-sem }()\n485:             c.Next()\n486:         default:\n487:             c.JSON(http.StatusTooManyRequests, gin.H{\n488:                 \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n489:                 \"code\":  \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\",\n490:             })\n491:             c.Abort()\n492:         }\n493:     }\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ---\n498: \n499: ## JWT Implementation\n500: \n501: ### Token Generation (`jwt.go`)\n502: \n503: ```go\n504: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n505:     now := time.Now()\n506:     \n507:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, jwt.MapClaims{\n508:         \"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n509:         \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n510:         \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n511:     })\n512:     \n513:     // Merge custom claims\n514:     for k, v := range claims {\n515:         token.Claims.(jwt.MapClaims)[k] = v\n516:     }\n517:     \n518:     return token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n519: }\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ### Secret Persistence\n523: \n524: ```go\n525: func (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n526:     if j.clientset == nil {\n527:         // Try in-cluster config\n528:         config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n529:         if err != nil {\n530:             klog.Warningf(\"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence: %v\", err)\n531:             return nil\n532:         }\n533:         j.clientset, err = kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n534:         if err != nil {\n535:             return err\n536:         }\n537:     }\n538:     \n539:     secret := &corev1.Secret{\n540:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n541:             Name:      IdentitySecretName,\n542:             Namespace: IdentityNamespace,\n543:             Labels: map[string]string{\n544:                 \"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n545:                 \"component\": \"router\",\n546:             },\n547:         },\n548:         Type: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n549:         Data: map[string][]byte{\n550:             PrivateKeyDataKey: encodePrivateKeyPEM(j.privateKey),\n551:             PublicKeyDataKey:  encodePublicKeyPEM(j.publicKey),\n552:         },\n553:     }\n554:     \n555:     _, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(ctx, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n556:     if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n557:         existing, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(ctx, IdentitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n558:         if err != nil {\n559:             return err\n560:         }\n561:         return j.loadPrivateKeyPEM(existing.Data[PrivateKeyDataKey])\n562:     }\n563:     return err\n564: }\n565: ```\n566: \n567: **Key Encoding:**\n568: - Private key: PKCS1 PEM format (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`)\n569: - Public key: PKIX PEM format (`PUBLIC KEY`)\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Testing Strategy\n574: \n575: ### Test Coverage Goals\n576: \n577: | Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n578: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n579: | `Server` | 80% | Construction, route registration, TLS, graceful shutdown |\n580: | `SessionManager` | 85% | Session resolution, Workload Manager create, error mapping |\n581: | `JWTManager` | 80% | Token generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence |\n582: | `ReverseProxy` | 85% | Director, forwarding headers, path normalization, error handler |\n583: | `Handlers` | 80% | Health endpoints, invocation routing, error responses |\n584: | `Middleware` | 75% | Concurrency limit, 429 response |\n585: \n586: ### Test Files\n587: \n588: | File | Purpose |\n589: |------|---------|\n590: | `server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health checks |\n591: | `session_manager_test.go` | GetSandboxBySession, create via Workload Manager, error cases |\n592: | `jwt_test.go` | Token generation, RS256 verification, secret CRUD |\n593: | `reverse_proxy_test.go` | Director, path normalization, header injection, error mapping |\n594: | `handlers_test.go` | Health endpoints, invocation handlers |\n595: | `middleware_test.go` | Concurrency limit, overload response |\n596: | `errors_test.go` | Error type construction, message formatting |\n597: \n598: ### Mock Dependencies\n599: \n600: ```go\n601: type MockStore struct {\n602:     GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc  func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n603:     StoreSandboxFunc           func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n604:     UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n605: }\n606: \n607: type MockSessionManager struct {\n608:     GetSandboxBySessionFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n609: }\n610: \n611: type MockJWTManager struct {\n612:     GenerateTokenFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n613: }\n614: \n615: type MockHTTPClient struct {\n616:     DoFunc func(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n617: }\n618: ```\n619: \n620: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n621: \n622: 1. **Session Resolution Flow**\n623:    - Request without session header ŌåÆ creates sandbox via Workload Manager\n624:    - Request with valid session header ŌåÆ lookup from store\n625:    - Request with invalid session ŌåÆ 404 response\n626: \n627: 2. **Proxy Flow**\n628:    - Successful proxy ŌåÆ response header with session ID\n629:    - Sandbox unreachable ŌåÆ 502 response\n630:    - Sandbox timeout ŌåÆ 504 response\n631: \n632: 3. **JWT Injection**\n633:    - Sandbox/SandboxClaim kind ŌåÆ JWT in Authorization header\n634:    - AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter ŌåÆ no JWT\n635: \n636: 4. **Concurrency Limit**\n637:    - Under limit ŌåÆ request processed\n638:    - At limit ŌåÆ 429 response\n639: \n640: 5. **Graceful Shutdown**\n641:    - Context cancel ŌåÆ shutdown within 10s deadline\n642:    - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n643: \n644: ---\n645: \n646: ## Validation Checklist\n647: \n648: - [ ] Config validates required fields (Port non-empty)\n649: - [ ] TLS requires both cert and key when EnableTLS=true\n650: - [ ] SessionManager requires WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n651: - [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens (verified by public key)\n652: - [ ] ReverseProxy Director normalizes paths correctly\n653: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps connection refused ŌåÆ 502\n654: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps timeout ŌåÆ 504\n655: - [ ] Health endpoints return correct JSON shapes\n656: - [ ] Concurrency middleware defaults to 1000 when config <= 0\n657: - [ ] Last-activity updated twice per invocation\n658: - [ ] Entry point selection handles empty list\n659: - [ ] Response header x-agentcube-session-id injected\n660: - [ ] Forwarding headers set correctly\n661: - [ ] Graceful shutdown respects 10s deadline\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ## Open Questions\n666: \n667: 1. **JWT Secret Rotation**: How to handle key rotation without disrupting active sessions?\n668:    - Proposal: Load both old and new keys, accept tokens signed by either\n669: \n670: 2. **Workload Manager Retry**: Should failed sandbox creation be retried?\n671:    - Current: Single attempt, client must retry\n672:    - Alternative: Add exponential backoff retry in SessionManager\n673: \n674: 3. **WebSocket Support**: Should Router proxy WebSocket upgrades?\n675:    - Current: Not supported (out of scope)\n676:    - Future: Add WebSocket upgrade handling in reverse_proxy.go\n677: \n678: 4. **Metrics Export**: Prometheus metrics for proxy latency, error rates?\n679:    - Current: Not in scope\n680:    - Future: Add middleware to record request duration and status codes\n681: \n682: ---\n683: \n684: ## References\n685: \n686: - `session-routing/spec.md` ŌĆö Full requirement specification\n687: - `session-routing/design.md` ŌĆö Detailed design document  \n688: - `session-store/design.md` ŌĆö Store interface and implementations\n689: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` ŌĆö SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n690: - `deployment/client-go.md` ŌĆö Kubernetes client code reference\n691: - `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` ŌĆö Workload Manager server pattern reference\n692: - `project.md` ŌĆö AgentCube architecture overview\n693: - Go `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n694: - `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt\n695: - Gin framework: https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin\n\n(End of file - total 695 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router HTTP reverse proxy core provides session-aware routing for AgentCube sandbox invocations. It resolves sessions via the store, creates new sandboxes through the Workload Manager when needed, reverse-proxies HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints, injects JWT tokens for sandbox authentication, and tracks activity for idle timeout detection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775849554761,"end":1775849554791}}}}
