{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849554800,"sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","part":{"id":"prt_d78e1c32d001uZ1IBLHbi5hyv9","messageID":"msg_d78e19e46001FcnbJ2ANajOOOM","sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-90c49ebd747044bc98a928948fb339eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session Resolution**: Reads session ID from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager when missing\n8: 2. **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n9: 3. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds\n10: 4. **Activity Tracking**: Updates session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle timeout detection\n11: 5. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware to prevent overload\n12: 6. **Health Endpoints**: Exposes `/health/live` and `/health/ready` for Kubernetes probes\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle management |\n21: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct (Port, EnableTLS, TLSCert, TLSKey, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug) |\n22: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface, manager struct with workload manager client |\n23: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with custom Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n24: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing, K8s Secret persistence |\n25: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/v1/...invocations/*path` handlers |\n26: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware using buffered channel semaphore |\n27: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types: SessionNotFoundError, SandboxUnreachableError, TimeoutError |\n28: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health endpoints tests |\n29: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Session resolution, workload manager create, error mapping tests |\n30: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Proxy director, forwarding headers, path normalization tests |\n31: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence tests |\n32: \n33: ### Key Components\n34: \n35: ```\n36: pkg/router/\n37: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Server (server.go)\n38: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Config struct (Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug)\n39: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ gin.Engine setup with mode (Debug/Release)\n40: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Route registration (health, invocation routes)\n41: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ http.Server with h2c, ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n42: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Start(ctx) with graceful shutdown (10s deadline)\n43: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Dependencies: SessionManager, Store, JWTManager, http.Transport\n44: Ōöé\n45: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ SessionManager (session_manager.go)\n46: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n47: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ manager struct with storeClient, workloadMgrAddr, httpClient\n48: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ NewSessionManager: reads WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL (required)\n49: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ createSandbox: POST to Workload Manager with optional K8s SA token\n50: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ HTTP client: Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 config\n51: Ōöé\n52: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Reverse Proxy (reverse_proxy.go)\n53: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy\n54: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Director: path normalization, Host, forwarding headers, JWT\n55: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ ModifyResponse: x-agentcube-session-id header injection\n56: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ ErrorHandler: connection refused ŌåÆ 502, timeout ŌåÆ 504\n57: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Entry point matching from SandboxInfo.EntryPoints\n58: Ōöé\n59: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ JWT Manager (jwt.go)\n60: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ RSA 2048-bit key generation (PKCS1 private, PKIX public)\n61: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ GenerateToken: exp (5m), iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\", custom claims\n62: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret: K8s Secret persistence/reuse\n63: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ RS256 signing with golang-jwt/v5\n64: Ōöé\n65: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Middleware (middleware.go)\n66: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ concurrencyLimitMiddleware: buffered channel semaphore\n67: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ MaxConcurrentRequests capacity (default 1000 when Ōēż0)\n68: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ 429 response when overloaded: SERVER_OVERLOADED code\n69: Ōöé\n70: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Handlers (handlers.go)\n71:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ handleHealthLive: 200 {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n72:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ handleHealthReady: 200/503 based on sessionManager nil\n73:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ handleInvoke: session resolution ŌåÆ proxy ŌåÆ activity update\n74:     ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ Error mapping: APIStatus ŌåÆ appropriate HTTP code\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Out of Scope\n78: \n79: - Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-00x)\n80: - Store implementation (covered by session-store spec)\n81: - Kubernetes Reconciler (AR-007)\n82: - Prometheus metrics export\n83: - Distributed session cache (Redis cluster)\n84: - WebSocket upgrade handling\n85: - Custom retry logic for failed proxies\n86: \n87: ## Impact Analysis\n88: \n89: ### Upstream Dependencies\n90: \n91: | Dependency | Impact |\n92: |------------|--------|\n93: | `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup, UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n94: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n95: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types |\n96: | `client-go` | kubernetes.Interface for JWT Secret management |\n97: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n98: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n99: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n100: | Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` for sandbox creation |\n101: \n102: ### Downstream Consumers\n103: \n104: | Consumer | Usage |\n105: |----------|-------|\n106: | `cmd/router/main.go` | CLI entry point, flag parsing, Server construction |\n107: | Kubernetes Deployment | Router as reverse proxy front-end to sandbox pods |\n108: | SDK/CLI clients | Invocation requests routed through Router |\n109: | `pkg/agentd` (idle cleanup) | Last-activity timestamps for idle detection |\n110: | Kubernetes probes | `/health/live`, `/health/ready` endpoints |\n111: \n112: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n113: \n114: - **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is contract; changing breaks all clients\n115: - **JWT Secret Name**: `picod-router-identity` Secret; migration needed if renamed\n116: - **Invocation Route Pattern**: `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` is fixed\n117: - **Response Header**: `x-agentcube-session-id` on proxied responses is client expectation\n118: - **Default Concurrency Limit**: 1000 when `MaxConcurrentRequests Ōēż 0`; affects throughput under load\n119: \n120: ## Alternatives Considered\n121: \n122: ### Alternative 1: Envoy Sidecar Proxy\n123: \n124: **Approach**: Deploy Envoy as sidecar to handle routing and load balancing.\n125: \n126: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n127: |--------|------------|\n128: | Pros | Production-grade proxy; rich routing features; observability built-in |\n129: | Cons | Heavy sidecar; no session-aware routing; requires xDS control plane; JWT signing complex |\n130: \n131: **Decision**: Rejected. Session-aware routing requires custom logic that Envoy cannot natively provide. In-process Go reverse proxy offers tighter integration with session management.\n132: \n133: ### Alternative 2: Nginx Ingress with Lua\n134: \n135: **Approach**: Use Nginx Ingress with Lua scripts for session routing and JWT injection.\n136: \n137: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n138: |--------|------------|\n139: | Pros | High performance; widely deployed; Nginx ecosystem |\n140: | Cons | Lua scripting complexity; no native store integration; debugging harder; JWT requires external helper |\n141: \n142: **Decision**: Rejected. Go-based proxy provides native integration with `pkg/store`, `pkg/common/types`, and Kubernetes client-go. Lua-based approach lacks tight coupling needed for session lifecycle.\n143: \n144: ### Alternative 3: API Gateway (Kong/Traefik)\n145: \n146: **Approach**: Use Kong or Traefik as API gateway for routing.\n147: \n148: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n149: |--------|------------|\n150: | Pros | Plugin ecosystem; declarative config; multi-protocol support |\n151: | Cons | External dependency; session store integration via plugin; JWT plugin limitations |\n152: \n153: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires session-stateful routing with direct store access. External gateway adds operational complexity and latency.\n154: \n155: ### Alternative 4: Custom HTTP Router with FastHTTP\n156: \n157: **Approach**: Use `fasthttp` instead of `net/http` for higher performance.\n158: \n159: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n160: |--------|------------|\n161: | Pros | Lower latency; zero-allocation design; high throughput |\n162: | Cons | Different API from `net/http`; httputil.ReverseProxy incompatible; Gin ecosystem mismatch |\n163: \n164: **Decision**: Rejected. `net/http` compatibility is required for `httputil.ReverseProxy` and Kubernetes client libraries. Gin middleware ecosystem (cors, recovery) is well-supported. Performance targets met with current stack.\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 5: Session-less Direct Routing\n167: \n168: **Approach**: Clients directly invoke sandbox pods without session abstraction.\n169: \n170: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n171: |--------|------------|\n172: | Pros | No session state; simpler architecture |\n173: | Cons | Clients must track pod endpoints; no idle timeout; no JWT injection; breaks SDK abstraction |\n174: \n175: **Decision**: Rejected. Session abstraction is core to AgentCube designŌĆöclients use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles physical routing (pod IPs) and lifecycle (creation/expiry).\n176: \n177: ## Risks\n178: \n179: | Risk | Mitigation |\n180: |------|------------|\n181: | Sandbox pod unreachable (connection refused) | ErrorHandler maps to 502 `sandbox unreachable` |\n182: | Sandbox timeout during proxy | ErrorHandler maps to 504 `sandbox timeout` |\n183: | JWT signing failure | Respond 500 with `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` code |\n184: | Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` missing; retry logic in session manager |\n185: | Secret creation race (multiple routers) | `AlreadyExists` handled by loading existing secret |\n186: | Concurrency limit exhaustion | 429 with `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code; client retry |\n187: | TLS misconfiguration | Start returns error if cert/key missing when `EnableTLS=true` |\n188: | Session not found in store | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n189: | Entry points empty | 404 `no entry point found for sandbox` |\n190: | Path normalization missing leading slash | Director prefixes `/` if needed |\n191: \n192: ## Implementation Notes\n193: \n194: 1. **Constants**: `rsaKeySize=2048`, `jwtExpiration=5m`, `IdentitySecretName=\"picod-router-identity\"`\n195: 2. **HTTP2**: `h2c` server with `http2.Server` for non-TLS HTTP/2 support\n196: 3. **Transport**: `IdleConnTimeout=0`, `DisableCompression=false`, shared across all proxies\n197: 4. **Session Manager HTTP Client**: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`, HTTP2 with `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n198: 5. **Workload Manager Auth**: Reads `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` for in-cluster auth\n199: 6. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default=\"default\")\n200: 7. **Last-Activity Updates**: Twice per invokeŌĆöafter sandbox resolution and after proxy completion\n201: 8. **Graceful Shutdown**: 10s deadline on context cancel\n202: 9. **Route Pattern**: Both GET and POST on invocation routes\n203: \n204: ## References\n205: \n206: - `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n207: - `session-routing/design.md` - Detailed design document\n208: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n209: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client code reference\n210: - `project.md` - AgentCube architecture overview\n211: - `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n212: - `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt\n\n(End of file - total 212 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads session ID from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager when missing\n2. **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n3. **JWT Authentication**: Generates RS256-signed JWT tokens for `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` kinds\n4. **Activity Tracking**: Updates session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle timeout detection\n5. **Concurrency Control**: Limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware to prevent overload\n6. **Health Endpoints**: Exposes `/health/live` and `/health/ready` for Kubernetes probes\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle management |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775849554769,"end":1775849554797}}}}
