{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849720164,"sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","part":{"id":"prt_d78e448e3001Zo0DwZ01UkYnpn","messageID":"msg_d78e2415e0012Y68S35gSr708G","sessionID":"ses_2871e815cffexSiKP2zwKM9zuY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b33b4b7b83664caf82cc49244cab797a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","content":"# AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 ŌĆö Router HTTP ÕÅŹÕÉæõ╗ŻńÉåµĀĖÕ┐ā |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Define error types in `errors.go`\n  - `SessionNotFoundError` with `SessionID` field, code `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`, HTTP 404\n  - `SandboxUnreachableError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`, HTTP 502\n  - `SandboxTimeoutError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`, HTTP 504\n  - `JWTSigningError` with `Err` field, code `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n  - `ServerOverloadedError` with code `SERVER_OVERLOADED`, HTTP 429\n  - `NoEntryPointError` with code `NO_ENTRY_POINT`, HTTP 404\n  - All errors implement `APIStatus` interface: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Define `APIStatus` interface\n  - Methods: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n  - All error types implement this interface\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestAPIStatus -v`\n\n### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n  - `Port int` (default 8080)\n  - `EnableTLS bool`\n  - `TLSCert string`\n  - `TLSKey string`\n  - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n  - `Debug bool`\n  - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n  - Returns `Config{Port: 8080, EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultConfig -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n  - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n  - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConstants -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Store Interface & Logger (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface for router\n  - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n  - File: `pkg/router/store.go` (or import from pkg/store)\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestStoreInterface -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface\n  - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n  - File: `pkg/router/logger.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggerInterface -v`\n\n### Phase 4: JWTManager (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTManager` interface\n  - `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace) (string, error)`\n  - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerInterface -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Define `jwtManager` struct\n  - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n  - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n  - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface`\n  - `namespace string`\n  - `logger Logger`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerStruct -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Implement RSA key generation\n  - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n  - Private key: PKCS1 PEM encoding\n  - Public key: PKIX PEM encoding\n  - Helper functions: `encodePrivateKeyPEM`, `encodePublicKeyPEM`, `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRSAKeyGeneration -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `NewJWTManager(kubeClient, namespace, logger)` constructor\n  - Generate RSA 2048-bit key pair\n  - Initialize struct with all fields\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)` method\n  - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n  - Add custom claims: `kind`, `name`, `namespace`\n  - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_GenerateToken -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n  - Create K8s Secret with name `picod-router-identity`\n  - Handle `AlreadyExists` by loading existing secret\n  - Load keys from secret data\n  - Use `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret -v`\n\n### Phase 5: SessionManager (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Define `SessionManager` interface\n  - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerInterface -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Define `manager` struct\n  - `storeClient Store`\n  - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n  - `httpClient *http.Client`\n  - `logger Logger`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestManagerStruct -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store, logger)` constructor\n  - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n  - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n  - Configure HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManager -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n  - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n  - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)`\n  - Return `SandboxInfo` or error\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n  - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n  - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n  - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n  - Add K8s SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` if available\n  - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `CreateSession`\n  - Use namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n  - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_createSandbox -v`\n\n### Phase 6: Middleware (ST-6)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1**: Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` function\n  - Use buffered channel as semaphore\n  - Capacity = `maxConcurrent` (default 1000 if <=0)\n  - `sem <- struct{}{}` to acquire slot\n  - `<-sem` to release slot (deferred)\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2**: Implement 429 overload response\n  - `select` with `default` case when semaphore full\n  - Return HTTP 429 with `{\"error\": \"server overloaded\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n  - Call `c.Abort()` to stop processing\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_Overload -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3**: Implement `loggingMiddleware` function\n  - Log request method, path, status, duration\n  - Use `logger.Info` with keys: method, path, status, duration\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.4**: Implement `recoveryMiddleware` function\n  - Recover from panics\n  - Log error with stack trace\n  - Return HTTP 500 with `{\"error\": \"internal server error\"}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRecoveryMiddleware -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Reverse Proxy (ST-7)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1**: Implement `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)` function\n  - Use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(target)`\n  - Set custom `Director` function\n  - Set custom `ModifyResponse` function\n  - Set custom `ErrorHandler` function\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2**: Implement `Director` function\n  - Path normalization: add leading `/` if missing\n  - Set `req.URL.Scheme`, `req.URL.Host`, `req.URL.Path`\n  - Set `req.Host` to target host\n  - Set forwarding headers: `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Real-IP`\n  - Inject JWT: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_Director -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3**: Implement `ModifyResponse` function\n  - Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n  - Value is the resolved session ID\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.4**: Implement `ErrorHandler` function\n  - Check for \"connection refused\" ŌåÆ HTTP 502 `sandbox unreachable`\n  - Check for \"timeout\" ŌåÆ HTTP 504 `sandbox timeout`\n  - Other errors ŌåÆ HTTP 500\n  - Return JSON response: `{\"error\": \"<message>\"}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.5**: Implement `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)` helper\n  - Find matching entry point by path prefix\n  - Default to first entry point if no match\n  - Return nil if `entryPoints` is empty\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSelectEntryPoint -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.6**: Implement `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)` helper\n  - Parse `entryPoint.Endpoint` as URL\n  - Add protocol prefix if missing: `entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + endpoint`\n  - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n\n### Phase 8: Handlers (ST-8)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1**: Implement `handleHealthLive(c)` handler\n  - Return HTTP 200\n  - Body: `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthLive -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2**: Implement `handleHealthReady(c)` handler\n  - Check if `sessionManager != nil`\n  - If nil: HTTP 503, body: `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}`\n  - If valid: HTTP 200, body: `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthReady -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3**: Implement `handleInvoke(c)` handler for invocation routing\n  - Extract `namespace`, `name`, `kind` from URL path params\n  - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - Call `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n  - Update activity: `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` (1st)\n  - Select entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n  - Generate JWT via `jwtManager.GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n  - Create reverse proxy and serve\n  - Update activity after proxy (2nd)\n  - Inject `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n  - Handle errors with appropriate HTTP codes\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4**: Implement `handleAgentInvoke(c)` handler\n  - Set `kind = AgentRuntimeKind`\n  - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleAgentInvoke -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.5**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke(c)` handler\n  - Set `kind = CodeInterpreterKind`\n  - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.6**: Implement `handleGetSandboxError(c, err)` helper\n  - Check `apierrors.IsNotFound` ŌåÆ HTTP 404\n  - Check `apierrors.APIStatus` ŌåÆ use status code from APIStatus\n  - Other errors ŌåÆ HTTP 500 with `\"internal server error\"`\n  - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleGetSandboxError -v`\n\n### Phase 9: Server (ST-9)\n\n- [ ] **T9.1**: Define `Server` struct\n  - `config *Config`\n  - `engine *gin.Engine`\n  - `httpServer *http.Server`\n  - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n  - `storeClient Store`\n  - `jwtManager JWTManager`\n  - `transport *http.Transport`\n  - `logger Logger`\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerStruct -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.2**: Implement `NewServer(config, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, logger)` constructor\n  - Create `engine := gin.New()`\n  - Set Gin mode: `gin.ReleaseMode` if `!config.Debug`, `gin.DebugMode` if `config.Debug`\n  - Initialize shared `http.Transport`\n  - Configure `httpServer` with h2c, `ReadTimeout=30s`, `IdleTimeout=90s`\n  - Register routes with middleware\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.3**: Implement route registration\n  - `/health/live` ŌåÆ `handleHealthLive` (no middleware)\n  - `/health/ready` ŌåÆ `handleHealthReady` (no middleware)\n  - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` ŌåÆ `handleAgentInvoke` (GET, POST)\n  - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` ŌåÆ `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` (GET, POST)\n  - Apply middleware: `concurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `loggingMiddleware`, `recoveryMiddleware`\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Routes -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.4**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method without TLS\n  - Configure h2c server with `http2.Server`\n  - Call `httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n  - Launch goroutine for graceful shutdown on context cancel\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Start -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.5**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method with TLS\n  - If `config.EnableTLS == true`: call `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)`\n  - Return error if cert/key files missing\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_StartTLS -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.6**: Implement graceful shutdown\n  - On context cancel: call `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n  - Shutdown deadline: 10s\n  - Server stops accepting new connections\n  - Existing connections complete before shutdown\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_GracefulShutdown -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.7**: Implement `Stop()` method\n  - Call `httpServer.Shutdown(ctx)` directly\n  - Use 10s timeout context\n  - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Stop -v`\n\n### Phase 10: Integration Tests (ST-10)\n\n- [ ] **T10.1**: Implement `handleInvoke` integration test\n  - Test session resolution flow without session header ŌåÆ creates sandbox\n  - Test session resolution with valid session header ŌåÆ lookup from store\n  - Test session resolution with invalid session ŌåÆ 404 response\n  - F